Four pillars: Encapsulation, Abstraction, Inheritance, Polymorphism

INHERITANCE
A class at the top of the hierarchy: superclass/base class/parent class
Class derived from another class: Subclass/extended class/child class
Inheritance promotes the concept of recycling code
e.g) A superclass named Animal with a subclass Cat
public class Animal {
    public void Move() {
        Console.WriteLine("I am walking!");
        }
    }
public class Cat : Animal { //Cat extends Animal
}
--Method Move() can be called from both Animal and Cat
--It is possible for multiple subclasses to inherit from one superclass

